        <headline>Flood Warning issued June 18 at 2:07AM CDT until June 22 at 11:30PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Kansas...

Neosho River Near Neosho Rapids affecting Lyon County.

* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Neosho River near Neosho Rapids.

* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon to late Sunday evening.

* IMPACTS...At 22.0 feet, Low lying areas along the river flood.
At 23.0 feet, Water overtops Road 145 on the west side of the
bridge over the Neosho River.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1:30 AM CDT Wednesday the stage was 17.8 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage
tomorrow afternoon to a crest of 22.9 feet Friday morning. It
will then fall below flood stage early Sunday morning.
- Flood stage is 22.0 feet.
</description>
        <instruction>

Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive
cars through flooded areas.

This product along with additional weather and stream information is
available at www.weather.gov/top/.</instruction>
